tps://web.archive.org/web/20210512043619/https://www.miamiherald.com/news/politics-government/article134490239.html}}</ref>以及[[佐治亚州众议院|州众议院]]民主党领袖[[史黛西艾布拉姆斯|史黛西·艾布拉姆斯]]的支持。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Democrat aiming for Tom Price's seat picks up key supporter|url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/democrat-aiming-for-tom-price-seat-picks-key-supporter/uvSP7I0glk0RhO1taiHMhK/|author=Bluestein|date=2017-02-09|first=Greg|work=[[The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution|The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20201218184657/https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/democrat-aiming-for-tom-price-seat-picks-key-supporter/uvSP7I0glk0RhO1taiHMhK/|archivedate=2020-12-18|accessdate=2021-01-06|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Jon Ossoff Doesn’t Live In The 6th District, But He Could Still Represent It|url=https://www.wabe.org/jon-ossoff-doesn-t-live-6th-district-he-could-still-represent-it/|accessdate=2021-01-06|date=2017-06-01|work=90.1 FM WABE|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512043616/https://www.wabe.org/jon-ossoff-doesn-t-live-6th-district-he-could-still-represent-it/}}</ref>他还得到了美国参议员和民主党总统候选人[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼桑德斯的]]公众支持。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sanders endorses Ossoff, but won't call him a progressive|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/329927-sanders-endorses-ossoff-but-wont-call-him-a-progressive|accessdate=2018-10-24|author=Sommer|date=2017-04-21|first=Will|archive-date=2022-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220318034428/https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/329927-sanders-endorses-ossoff-but-wont-call-him-a-progressive}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-reload-for-georgia-runoff-but-party-divisions-remain-1492626238|title=Democrats Reload for Georgia Runoff, But Party Divisions Remain|first=Reid J.|author=Epstein|first2=Natalie|author2=Andrews|date=2017-04-19|work=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]]|accessdate=2018-10-24|archive-date=2022-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220428191504/https://www.wsj.com/articles/democrats-reload-for-georgia-runoff-but-party-divisions-remain-1492626238}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Sanders clarifies support for Ossoff after dustup|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/democrats-vs-trump/bernie-sanders-clarifies-support-jon-ossoff-after-dustup-n749491|accessdate=2018-10-24|author=Seitz-Wald|date=2017-04-21|first=Alex|archive-date=2021-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512043655/https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/democrats-vs-trump/bernie-sanders-clarifies-support-jon-ossoff-after-dustup-n749491}}</ref>到当年4月初，奥索夫已筹集到了830万美元。<ref>{{Cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170406103448/https://www.myajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/ossoff-pulls-record-donations-for-georgia-special-election/MqGzLMjrzVRR8jE5YGs3rL/|date=2017-04-05|first=Aaron|author=Gould Sheinin|first2=Greg|author2=Bluestein|archivedate=2017-04-06|url=https://www.myajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/ossoff-pulls-record-donations-for-georgia-special-election/MqGzLMjrzVRR8jE5YGs3rL/|title=Democrat Ossoff rakes in huge amount in 6th District race|work=[[The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution|The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|accessdate=2017-04-06|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>

根据《亚特兰大宪法杂志》报道，奥索夫“将原本预计将是一场平静的，获得一个长期安全的共和党席位的竞选，变成了一场关于[[唐納·川普|特朗普]]，医疗保健改革和郊区党派斗争的代理人战斗。”<ref name="preps">{{Cite web|title=Handel preps another 6th District campaign as Ossoff hints at comeback|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/handel-preps-another-6th-district-campaign-ossoff-hints-comeback/PsDYoQhTSRIsq6myncmmuO/|accessdate=2020-12-18|author=Bluestein|date=2017-08-03|first=Greg|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200610124617/https://www.ajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/handel-preps-another-6th-district-campaign-ossoff-hints-comeback/PsDYoQhTSRIsq6myncmmuO/|archivedate=2020-06-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>当他参加竞选时，[[库克党派投票指数|库克党派投票指数]]将佐治亚州的第六届国会选区评为偏共和党14点。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Partisan Voting Index: Districts of the 113th Congress|url=http://cookpolitical.com/file/2013-04-49.pdf|accessdate=2020-04-17|date=2013|work=[[The_Cook_Political_Report|The Cook Political Report]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617193745/http://cookpolitical.com/file/2013-04-49.pdf|archivedate=2017-06-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>该地区不被认为具有竞争力，并且该区自1978年以来一直由共和党代表。<ref>{{Cite web|title=When Was the Last Time a Democrat Represented Georgia's Sixth Congressional District?|url=https://heavy.com/news/2017/04/georgia-sixth-congressional-district-last-most-recent-democrat-jon-ossoff/|author=Morrow|date=2017-04-18|first=Brendan|work=[[Heavy.com|Heavy]]|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2021-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211123080434/https://heavy.com/news/2017/04/georgia-sixth-congressional-district-last-most-recent-democrat-jon-ossoff/}}</ref>在奥索夫宣布前不到两个月，普莱斯还以62%的得票率，以压倒性优势连任。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/elections/2016/results/georgia-house-district-6-price-stooksbury|date=2017-08-01|title=Georgia U.S. House 6th District Results: Tom Price Wins|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2022-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313200019/https://www.nytimes.com/elections/2016/results/georgia-house-district-6-price-stooksbury}}</ref>

奥索夫在第6区长大，他的家人仍居住在那里，不过截至选举时，他仍住在该区边界外约2.4公里的地方。奥索夫解释说，他暂时住在邻近的第4区，以便他的同居女友（当时是[[埃默里大學|埃默里大學]]的医科学生）可以步行上班。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/18/politics/georgia-candidate-shrugs-off-district-issues-cnntv/index.html|title=Dem hopeful dismisses questions about residency|first=Josiah|author=Ryan|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|date=2017-04-18|accessdate=2017-04-18|archive-date=2021-12-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211220223203/https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/18/politics/georgia-candidate-shrugs-off-district-issues-cnntv/index.html}}</ref><ref name="db-2017-03-01">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/could-the-resistance-start-with-georgias-special-election|title=Could The Resistance Start With Georgia's Special Election?|author=Murphy|first=Patricia|date=2017-02-27|work=The Daily Beast|accessdate=2017-03-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Robert|author=Costa|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/georgia-house-race-stokes-gop-identity-crisis--and-opportunity-for-democrats/2017/04/18/a2231a48-242f-11e7-b503-9d616bd5a305_story.html|title=Republicans avoid big loss by forcing runoff in Ga. House race|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=2017-04-18|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2021-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512043814/https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/georgia-house-race-stokes-gop-identity-crisis--and-opportunity-for-democrats/2017/04/18/a2231a48-242f-11e7-b503-9d616bd5a305_story.html}}</ref>两人在竞选期间订婚。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fox5atlanta.com/news/jon-ossoff-engaged-to-long-time-girlfriend-amid-6th-district-race|date=2017-05-08|title=Jon Ossoff engaged to long-time girlfriend amid 6th District Race|work=Fox 5|accessdate=2020-11-05|archive-date=2021-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512043807/https://www.fox5atlanta.com/news/jon-ossoff-engaged-to-long-time-girlfriend-amid-6th-district-race}}</ref>
