2017年4月18日，在初选中没有候选人获得50%的选票。<ref name="CNNShort">{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/18/politics/georgia-house-6th-special-election-jon-ossoff/index.html|date=2017-04-19|title=Ossoff falls just short in Georgia special election|first=Eric|author=Bradner|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|accessdate=2017-04-19|archive-date=2021-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211008170058/https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/18/politics/georgia-house-6th-special-election-jon-ossoff/index.html}}</ref>奥索夫以大约48.1％的选票领先，共和党候选人凯伦·汉德尔（Karen Handel）获得了19.8％，其余选票则分散给了其他16名候选人。<ref name="GASOS04192017">{{Cite news|date=2017-04-19|title=Unofficial Results|url=https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/GA/67317/Web02-state/|publisher=Georgia Secretary of State|location=Atlanta, Georgia|accessdate=2017-04-19|archive-date=2022-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220211528/https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/GA/67317/Web02-state/}}</ref> <ref name="NYTApril">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/elections/results/georgia-house-special-election-district-6|title=Election Results: Ossoff, Handel Advance in Race for Georgia's Sixth Congressional District|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2017-04-19|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2022-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220220211529/https://www.nytimes.com/elections/results/georgia-house-special-election-district-6}}</ref>由于没有候选人获得绝对多数席位，因此排名前两位的投票者奥索夫和汉德尔参加了2017年6月20日举行的[[两轮选举制|第二轮选举]]。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=The Voter's Self Defense System|url=https://justfacts.votesmart.org/candidate/political-courage-test/176134/jon-ossoff/|accessdate=2017-04-20|work=Vote Smart|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108041145/https://justfacts.votesmart.org/candidate/political-courage-test/176134/jon-ossoff/}}</ref>奥索夫赢得了除1%的民主党选票之外的所有选票，而共和党的选票则更加分散。共和党人总共赢得了51.2%的总票数。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ossoff Falls Short of a Majority in Georgia House Race, Heads to Runoff|url=https://nymag.com/intelligencer/2017/04/ossoff-to-face-handel-in-georgia-special-election-runoff.html|accessdate=2017-05-11|author=Kilgore|date=2017-04-19|first=Ed|work=[[New_York_(magazine)|New York]]|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112024330/http://nymag.com/intelligencer/2017/04/ossoff-to-face-handel-in-georgia-special-election-runoff.html}}</ref>

奥索夫打破了[[美国众议院|美国众议院]]候选人的全国筹款纪录。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/09/us/politics/ossoff-handel-georgia-house-special-election.html|first=Jonathan|author=Martin|first2=Rachel|author2=Shorey|title=Ossoff Raises $23 Million in Most Expensive House Race in History|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2017-06-09|accessdate=2017-07-13|archive-date=2021-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211122161741/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/09/us/politics/ossoff-handel-georgia-house-special-election.html}}</ref>他的竞选活动总共筹集了超过2300万美元，其中三分之二来自全美的小额捐助者。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jon Ossoff, the Congressional Candidate Social Media Built|url=https://www.wired.com/story/ossoff-social-media-campaign/|accessdate=2017-07-13|author=Lapowsky|date=2017-06-21|first=Issie|work=[[Wired_(magazine)|Wired]]|archive-date=2021-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210617164204/https://www.wired.com/story/ossoff-social-media-campaign/}}</ref>他的对手汉德尔和[[共和黨_(美國)|共和党]]全国组织抨击他从[[佐治亚州|佐治亚州]]以外筹集了可观的小额捐款，尽管汉德尔的竞选活动得到了超级[[政治行動委員會|政治行动委员会]]和其他外部团体的支持，包括一些匿名资助的钱。<ref>{{Cite web|title=In GA-6 race, fact-checking attacks about campaign cash|url=https://www.politifact.com/article/2017/jun/08/ga-6-race-fact-checking-attacks-campaign-cash/|accessdate=2017-07-13|author=Greenber|date=2017-06-08|first=Jon|work=[[Politifact|Politifact]]|archive-date=2021-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210614171155/https://www.politifact.com/article/2017/jun/08/ga-6-race-fact-checking-attacks-campaign-cash/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Guess who's funding multimillion-dollar ad blitzes slamming Ossoff's out-of-state donors?|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2017/6/19/15827686/georgia-election-ossoff-money|accessdate=2017-07-13|author=Stein|date=2017-06-19|first=Jeff|work=[[Vox_(website)|Vox]]|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211032509/https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2017/6/19/15827686/georgia-election-ossoff-money}}</ref>竞选活动和外部团体代表的支出加起来超过了5500万美元，这是美国历史上最昂贵的[[美国众议院|众议院]]选举。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/06/20/us/politics/georgia-6th-most-expensive-house-election.html|title=Who Financed the Georgia Sixth, the Most Expensive House Election Ever|author=Parlapiano|first=Alicia|date=2017-06-20|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2017-06-23|author2=Shorey|first2=Rachel|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2022-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220428191504/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/06/20/us/politics/georgia-6th-most-expensive-house-election.html}}</ref>在竞选期间，共和党的战略重点是将他与民主党领袖[[南希·佩洛西|南希·佩洛西]]联系起来，后者在共和党人中两极分化，不受欢迎。奥索夫拒绝透露如果当选他是否会支持佩洛西就任[[美國眾議院議長|众议院议长]]。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/06/21/politics/republicans-nancy-pelosi-georgia/index.html|title=Trump and Republicans Don't Want Pelosi To Go|author=Bradner|first=Eric|date=2017-06-22|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|accessdate=2017-10-24|archive-date=2021-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210915154349/https://edition.cnn.com/2017/06/21/politics/republicans-nancy-pelosi-georgia/index.html}}</ref>

在6月20日的二次选举中，奥索夫被汉德尔（Handel）击败，他的对手得到了51.78％，而他获得了48.22％。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Election Night Reporting|url=https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/GA/70059/Web02-state/#/|work=results.enr.clarityelections.com|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2020-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118095035/https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/GA/70059/Web02-state/#/}}</ref>据《亚特兰大杂志》报道，“雖然他在總票數中的百分比從4月到現在都保持穩定，但奧索夫在這三個月中獲得了32,220張選票，增加了34%....奥索夫和他的盟友可能已经挖走了所有支持民主党人的选票...但这仍然不足以克服共和党的数字优势。” <ref>{{Cite web|title=Planned Parenthood's $800,000 fight to get Jon Ossoff elected wasn't enough|url=https://www.atlantamagazine.com/news-culture-articles/planned-parenthoods-800000-fight-get-jon-ossoff-elected-wasnt-enough/|accessdate=2020-12-18|author=Henry|date=2017-06-21|first=Scott|archive-date=2021-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210623045342/https://www.atlantamagazine.com/news-culture-articles/planned-parenthoods-800000-fight-get-jon-ossoff-elected-wasnt-enough/}}</ref> 《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道说，他“可能是至少十年来在年度选举中最强大的民主党人”，“为民主党带来了数量惊人的年轻和非白人选民” <ref name="auto">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/26/upshot/why-strong-turnout-was-not-enough-for-democrats-in-georgia.html|title=Democrats' Turnout in Georgia Blew Past Typical Off-Year Levels|first=Nate|author=Cohn|date=2017-06-26|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2022-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220428094154/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/26/upshot/why-strong-turnout-was-not-enough-for-democrats-in-georgia.html}}</ref> ，并使第六区的青年投票率比2014年中期选举时增加了近一倍。但是，根据《亚特兰大宪法杂志》的报道，“在一个共和党人数远远超过民主党的地区，激增的民主党投票人数还是不足以克服共和党的人数。” <ref name="preps"/>在报道选举结果后，弗兰克·布鲁尼（Frank Bruni）在《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的专栏文章中将这次竞选描述为“挫伤了民主党人的士气”。<ref>{{Cite news|first=Frank|author=Bruni|authorlink=Frank Bruni|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/20/opinion/georgia-election-karen-handel-jon-ossoff.html|title=After Georgia Election, Democrats Are Demoralized, Again|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2017-06-20|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2022-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126174254/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/20/opinion/georgia-election-karen-handel-jon-ossoff.html}}</ref>这是自1992年该区成为目前的独立郊区选区以来，民主党人离赢得该区胜利最接近的一次。民主党挑战者在此之前仅两次赢得超过40%的选票。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Our Campaigns – Container Detail Page|url=https://www.ourcampaigns.com/ContainerHistory.html?ContainerID=421|accessdate=2017-05-11|publisher=ourcampaigns.com|archive-date=2021-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210624064454/https://www.ourcampaigns.com/ContainerHistory.html?ContainerID=421}}</ref>

