在11月的大选中，两位候选人均未获得50％的选票，迫使在2021年1月5日举行额外的特殊选举。<ref name="ajc11052020">{{Cite news|author=Bluestein|first=Greg|title=Ossoff, Perdue appear headed for runoff in Georgia|url=https://www.ajc.com/politics/nbc-makes-call-ossoff-perdue-head-for-runoff-in-georgia/675VCH4CEVGWFLWIHZLZE52NKU/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201221154331/https://www.ajc.com/politics/nbc-makes-call-ossoff-perdue-head-for-runoff-in-georgia/675VCH4CEVGWFLWIHZLZE52NKU/|archivedate=2020-12-21|work=[[The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution|The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|date=2020-11-05|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":9">{{Cite news|author=Fausset|first=Richard|author2=Epstein|first2=Reid J.|date=2020-06-10|title=Jon Ossoff Wins Democratic Senate Primary in Georgia|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/10/us/politics/jon-ossoff-georgia-senate.html|accessdate=2020-06-11|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>自2020年10月以来，奥索夫为竞选筹集了超过1亿美元，使他成为美国历史上资金最雄厚的参议院候选人。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Rojas|first=Rick|date=2020-12-25|title=Democrats in Georgia Runoffs Bring in Record Haul|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/25/us/politics/georgia-senate-record-fundraising.html|accessdate=2021-01-02|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2022-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518034542/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/12/25/us/politics/georgia-senate-record-fundraising.html}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Democrats shatter fundraising records ahead of Georgia Senate runoffs|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/12/24/democrats-fundraising-records-georgia-senate-runoffs-450440|accessdate=2021-01-02|work=POLITICO|language=en|archive-date=2021-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210710221823/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/12/24/democrats-fundraising-records-georgia-senate-runoffs-450440}}</ref>在奥索夫竞选的最后争论集中在两千美金经济刺激救助金，他和[[拉斐尔·沃诺克|拉斐尔·沃诺克]]表示如果他们赢得了选举，民主党多数将在参议院批准该举措。<ref>{{Cite web|title=In Georgia, Democrats close with populist pitch vowing $2,000 stimulus checks|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/georgia-democrats-close-populist-pitch-vowing-2-000-stimulus-checks-n1252805|accessdate=2021-01-05|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141559/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/georgia-democrats-close-populist-pitch-vowing-2-000-stimulus-checks-n1252805|dead-url=no}}</ref>

