奥索夫支持《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|平价医疗法案]]》（也称为“奥巴马医改”）。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=The Voter's Self Defense System|url=https://justfacts.votesmart.org/candidate/political-courage-test/176134/jon-ossoff/|accessdate=2017-04-20|work=Vote Smart}}</ref>他的医疗保健政策包括三项原则：“第一，任何美国人都不得因可预防或可治疗的疾病而遭受痛苦或死亡。第二，没有人会因生病而破产。第三，任何企业都不应因为不能支付[[醫療保險|醫療保險]]费而导致破产或不得不解雇雇员。” <ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=How top Sixth District contenders stack up on healthcare, taxes and transportation|url=http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2017/04/17/how-top-sixth-district-contenders-stack-up-on-healthcare-taxes-and-transportation/|author=Bluestein|date=2017-04-17|first=Greg|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421003349/http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2017/04/17/how-top-sixth-district-contenders-stack-up-on-healthcare-taxes-and-transportation/|archivedate=2017-04-21|accessdate=2021-01-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>他不支持推动采用[[單一支付者醫療衛生系統|单一付款人的医疗保健]]系统，例如美国全民医疗保险（Medicare for All）。<ref name="sharper">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/06/08/us/politics/georgia-special-election-ossoff-handel.html|title=Takeaways From the Georgia Special Election Debate: A Sharper Clash|author=Burns|first=Alexander|date=2017-06-08|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2017-06-13|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name="Axios 2010-11-10">{{Cite news|author=Talev|first=Margaret|date=2010-11-10|title=Jon Ossoff: Georgia opponent Sen. David Perdue embodies "Trumpism in a nutshell"|work=Axios|publisher=Axios|url=https://www.axios.com/jon-ossoff-georgia-senate-runoffs-axios-on-hbo-08be103c-ff01-40b7-98b9-e3d694d62b21.html|accessdate=2020-11-11}}</ref>他反对2017年3月版和2017年5月版的《[[2017年美国保健法案|美国卫生保健法]]》，这是众议院共和党的法案，该法案将废除了《平价医疗法案》。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Elise Viebeck & David Weigel|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/gop-candidate-now-embracing-trump-in-georgias-6th-district-runoff/2017/04/30/28a89bb0-2c5f-11e7-b605-33413c691853_story.html|work=The Washington Post|date=2017-04-30|title=GOP candidate now embracing Trump in Georgia's 6th District runoff|accessdate=2021-01-06|archive-date=2021-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210108113038/https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/gop-candidate-now-embracing-trump-in-georgias-6th-district-runoff/2017/04/30/28a89bb0-2c5f-11e7-b605-33413c691853_story.html}}</ref>他说，2017年5月的版本比先前的法案更糟，“因为它对那些有[[既有身體狀況|既有身体状况的人]]的保护更少。”<ref>{{Cite web|title=A 6th District rift over the House healthcare plan in Tom Price's old turf|url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/6th-district-rift-over-the-house-healthcare-plan-tom-price-old-turf/WVVQblWFJTRe6iWdexKljJ/|author=Greg Bluestein|date=2016-05-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722202652/https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/6th-district-rift-over-the-house-healthcare-plan-tom-price-old-turf/WVVQblWFJTRe6iWdexKljJ/|archivedate=2019-07-22|accessdate=2021-01-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>

